    "Question 3:\n",
    "\n",
    "1) Load the data from the two provided files 'books.pkl' and 'movies.pkl', which contain some information\n",
    "   about the top 3 books/movies from the last decade (according to some chatbot...). Use a context manager when loading.\n",
    "   Look at what you have loaded and make yourself familiar with the data structure.\n",
    "\n",
    "2) Create a class to store information about media, which at object creation time takes as input title, year and type (book or movie).\n",
    "   Add a method which prints out that information in a short sentence.\n",
    "\n",
    "3) Create a second class that is more specific for books, which inherits from your first class.\n",
    "   At object creation time it should not need the type as input, but title and year. Additionally, it needs the author and number of pages.\n",
    "   Now add a method to print more detailed information, which calls the original method from the parent class (do not polymorph!)\n",
    "   and additionally prints some sentence about who wrote the book and how many pages it has.\n",
    "\n",
    "4) Do a comparable thing with a class for movies instead of books. In this one, you will have director and runtime instead of author and pages.\n",
    "   When printing detailed information, you should change the format of the runtime (given in minutes) to a nicer looking combination of hours and minutes.\n",
    "\n",
    "5) Now use the loaded data to create book and movie objects for all provided entries. Then print their detailed information."
